Current Windows server is Windows Server 2025.
Uses NTFS (New Technology File System)
Previously FAT16/32 (File Allocation Table) and HPFS (High Performance File System)
NTFS is a journalling filesystem - it can repair files/folders using information previously stored in logs
Environment variables store information about the OS, such as OS path, number of processors to be used by OS, locations of temp folders etc.
System environment variable is %windir%
Privileged mode for users is standard for Administator Users. User Account Control (UAC).
Settings was first introduced with Windows 8 but Control Panel still offers more control and actions over the computer. Some Settings options also escalate to Control Panel.

