System Configuration (MSConfig)
Windows servers do not handle start up apps like Windows clients do
To view them:
- Win + R
- Type shell:startup
Windows uses an extra paging file as VRAM when the physical RAM becomes full to prevent delays and slowdown
To view/modify the page file:
- View advanced system settings -> System Properties 
- Navigate to Advanced tab
- Click Settings under Performance tab
Windows creates a crash dump file when it encounters an error like the BSOD
You can find its settings in Startup and Recovery
You can change UAC settings
